The paper discusses the use of inverse dynamics in robotics and biomechanics applications, specifically in the context of robot control. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of established phenomenological models like Coulomb friction, which suggests that it may also belong to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category. The paper also uses virtual robots and sensor data from simulation, which suggests that it may belong to the Learning (cs.LG), Computer Vision (cs.CV), or Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories.
